!Common Include for restarting events after full system outage. !:SET &ITEM# = JOBP.TESTED.RENAMED12 !First we need Time Processing. :SET &TIME# = SYS_TIME("HH:MM:SS", "PST") : PRINT Here is the difference now and midnight &TIME# :SET &DATE# = SYS_DATE("YYYY-MM-DD") : PRINT Here is todays Date &DATE# :SET &ACTVAR# = VARA.SQL.LOOPING :SET &COL# = 2 :SET &PERIOD# = GET_VAR(&ACTVAR#, &ITEM#, &COL#) : PRINT Here is the midnight start offset: &PERIOD# :SET &MIN1# = SYS_TIME("MM:SS") : PRINT Current minute is &MIN1# !Now we need to set current or next hour Processing. :IF "&MIN1#" > "&PERIOD#" : PRINT &MIN1# IS GREATER THAN &PERIOD# : SET &HOUR# = SYS_TIME("HH", "PST") : PRINT Here is the Hour now &HOUR# : SET &ACTHOUR# = ADD(&HOUR#, "1") : PRINT Here is the "before formatting" ACTHOUR: &ACTHOUR# : SET &ACTHOUR#=FORMAT(&ACTHOUR#) : SET &ACTHOUR#=FORMAT("&ACTHOUR#", "00") : ELSE : SET &HOUR# = SYS_TIME("HH", "PST") : PRINT Here is the Hour now &HOUR# : PRINT Here is the "before formatting" ACTHOUR: &ACTHOUR# : SET &ACTHOUR# = &HOUR# : SET &ACTHOUR#=FORMAT("&ACTHOUR#", "00") :ENDIF
:SET &ACTTIME# = "&DATE# &ACTHOUR#:&PERIOD#" : PRINT Here is the next available hour Activation Time: &ACTTIME# !Now we have the activate time, we can continue with object procesing. :SET &ACTOBJ# = ACTIVATE_UC_OBJECT(&ITEM#,,,,"&ACTTIME#")
